1. *Zatvorenik* je pobegao iz zatvora. (The *prisoner* escaped from the prison.)
2. Sudija je presudio da će *zatvorenik* morati da izdržava kaznu zatvora. (The judge ruled that the *inmate* would have to serve a prison sentence.)
3. *Zatvorenik* je u svojoj ćeliji. (The *convict* is in his cell.)
4. Policija je uhapsila *zatvorenika* koji je prekršio uslovnu kaznu. (The police arrested the *detainee* who violated his probation.)
5. Advokat se sastao sa svojim *zatvorenikom* pre suđenja. (The lawyer met with his *client* before the trial.)
6. Psiholozi su proučavali ponašanje *zatvorenika* u zatvorskom okruženju. (Psychologists studied the behavior of *prisoners* in a prison environment.)
7. *Zatvorenik* je dobio pomilovanje posle dugogodišnjeg boravka u zatvoru. (The *inmate* was granted clemency after spending many years in prison.)
8. Država je izdvojila novac za poboljšanje uslova boravka *zatvorenika* u zatvorima. (The state allocated funds to improve the living conditions of *convicts* in prisons.)
9. *Zatvorenik* je priznao krivicu pred sudom. (The *detainee* admitted guilt in court.)
10. Poverenik za ljudska prava je izrazio zabrinutost zbog lošeg tretmana *zatvorenika* u zatvorima. (The human rights commissioner expressed concern about the poor treatment of *inmates* in prisons.)